article.headline: TCU 62, SMU 44
article.story: FORT WORTH, Texas -- Edvinas Ruzgas scored 13 points and had 7 rebounds to lead Texas Christian to a 62-44 win over Southern Methodist on Wednesday night. The Horned Frogs led 35-25 at the half and turned up the defense to hold SMU (2-3) to 19 points in the second half. The Mustangs didn't help themselves with 21 turnovers that led to 27 points for TCU (3-3). Ronnie Moss joined Ruzgas in double figures with 12 points and three rebounds. Derek Williams led SMU in scoring with 16 points. Williams was 6-of-13 for the night.
